1) Installed gcc-multilib in order to compile the program on my 64 bit Ubuntu machine.
1.1 sudo apt-get install gcc-multilib


2) Added symbol files for the CFLAGS arguments by adding the -g to the CFLAGS in the Makefile provided

3) In order to be able to debug the application did the following:
$ sudo su (password)
$ echo 0 > /proc/sys/kernel/yama/ptrace_scope
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22749015/cannot-debug-with-gdb-in-ubuntu

4) General links:
4.1) EIP register:
https://security.stackexchange.com/questions/129499/what-does-eip-stand-for

4.2) Heap overflow vulnerability example:
https://samsclass.info/127/proj/p7-heap0.htm

4.3) mcheck man page:
https://linux.die.net/man/3/mcheck

4.4) LD_PRELOAD usage example:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/426230/what-is-the-ld-preload-trick

4.5) Official GNU malloc_check documentation:
https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Heap-Consistency-Checking.html

4.6) Check if ASLR is set in the kernel:
$ cat /proc/sys/kernel/randomize_va_space // output of 2 means it is activated.

4.7) Malloc debug example:
https://android.googlesource.com/platform/bionic/+/master/libc/malloc_debug/README.md

4.8) GCC security features:
https://blogs.oracle.com/linux/post/making-code-more-secure-with-gcc-part-2

4.9) Adding security checks for GCC (add it to the CFLAGS in the Makefile):
-fstack-protector-strong
